                  <persName id="t18321129-239-person2063">
                  WILLIAM 
                  FORD
               <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2063" type="surname" value="FORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2063" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2063" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am errand-boy to Thomas Lee, of <placeName id="t18321129-239-crimeloc1343">Collingwood-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18321129-239-crimeloc1343" type="placeName" value="Collingwood-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18321129-239-crimeloc1343" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321129-239-off1341 t18321129-239-crimeloc1343"></join>. I went to Mr. Harris', and ordered half a hundred of coals; the prisoner, who is his <rs id="t18321129-239-deflabel1344" type="occupation">errand-boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321129-239-defend2060 t18321129-239-deflabel1344"></join>, brought them to my mistress' door - my mistress gave me a sovereign to pay for them; when I got to the door - he told me to toss the sovereign up, and see how bright it would look; I tossed it up, and it fell on the stones - I ran, and got a light; I left him there the while, and then we got a birch broom, and all looked for it, but we never found it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-239-person2064">
                  ELIZA 
                  LEE
               <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2064" type="surname" value="LEE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2064" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2064" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I gave this boy the sovereign - he came and said he had dropped it; I found the prisoner at the door, looking for it, but we could not find it - I have never seen it since; the prisoner said it did not roll.</p>
               <p>THOMAS LEE. The sovereigns was mine - it was lost on Saturday night; I saw the prisoner when it was lost; I sent for him the following morning, and he had a pair of new boots on - I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-239-person2065">
                  RICHARD 
                  HUNT
               <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2065" type="surname" value="HUNT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2065" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2065" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable H 70). I had information, and went to the prisoner's mother on Sunday evening, and found her very much in liquor, laying on the floor - the prisoner was not at home; I asked her where he was, but she was too drunk to tell me - I went out, saw him in the street, and took him into custody; I asked him if he had had the sovereign - he said No; I asked him again, and he said Yes, he had - I asked what he had done with it; he pointed to a bird and cage, and said that was part of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-239-person2066">
                  JAMES 
                  JOHN CONNELLY
               <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2066" type="surname" value="JOHN CONNELLY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2066" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-239-person2066" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable H 135). I have the bird and cage, cap, and boots; the inspector was booking the charge, and asked the prisoner what he had done with it - he said he had had the sovereign, and bought a pair of new boots, a cap, and some fire-works; he gave his mother 1s. 6d., and his father 4s; I was sent to the house, and found his father and mother both intoxicated; I brought the bird and cage, fire-works, and cap down to the office - his father and mother were discharged.</p>
               <p>
